{"info": {"author": "Dustin Ingram", "author_email": "di@python.org", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "description": "# corvid\n\ncorvid is an opinionated simple static site generator.\n\nIt processes Markdown files, static assets and directories producing a 1:1\nheiarchy of compiled content.\n\nIt includes a reloadable local development server, supports custom markdown frontmatter and Jinja templates.\n\n## Installation\n\n```\n$ pip install corvid\n```\n\n## Running\n\nBy default corvid expects to be run in a directory with an `input` directory. With no parameters, corvid will process all files in this directory into the `output` directory, and exit.\n\n```\n$ corvid --help\nUsage: corvid [OPTIONS]\n\nOptions:\n  -l, --listen          Enable live reloading\n  -b, --bind TEXT       Host to bind to\n  -p, --port INTEGER    Port to run on\n  -i, --input TEXT      Input directory\n  -o, --output TEXT     Output directory\n  -t, --templates TEXT  Templates directory\n  --help                Show this message and exit.\n```\n\n## Example\n\nGiven the following directory layout:\n\n```\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 input\n\u2502\u00a0\u00a0 \u2514\u2500\u2500 index.md\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 templates\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 default.html\n```\nWith the following file contents:\n\n`input/index.md`\n```\n---\ntitle: This is the Index\n---\n\nWelcome\n```\n\n`templates/default.html`\n```html\n<html>\n    <head>\n        <title>{{ title }}</title>\n    <body>\n        {{ content }}\n    </body>\n</body>\n```\n\nRunning `corvid` will produce the additional `output` directory:\n\n```\n.\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 input\n\u2502\u00a0\u00a0 \u2514\u2500\u2500 index.md\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 output\n\u2502\u00a0\u00a0 \u2514\u2500\u2500 index.html\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 templates\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 default.html\n```\n\nAnd the contents of the file will be:\n\n`output/index.html`\n```html\n<html>\n    <head>\n        <title>This is the Index</title>\n    <head>\n    <body>\n        <p>Welcome</p>\n    </body>\n</body>\n```\n\n## Using templates\n\nCustom templates can be set by specifying the path to the template inside the `templates` directory as the `template` frontmatter.\n\nSee [`/example`](/example) for a full example.\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/di/corvid", "keywords": "static markdown", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "corvid", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/corvid/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/corvid/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/di/corvid"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/corvid/1.0.0/", "requires_dist": ["click (>=7.0<=8.0)", "python-frontmatter (>=0.5.0)", "Markdown (>=3.1)", "jinja2 (>=2.10)", "watchdog (>=0.9.0)", "pytest ; extra == 'test'", "tox ; extra == 'test'"], "requires_python": ">=3.5, <4", "summary": "An opinionated simple static site generator", "version": "1.0.0"}, "last_serial": 6441603, "releases": {"1.0.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "2e7f8722779bedc8f6e380c974c5f8fe", "sha256": "0bc3e050a99584da31681762c9579e97c7d11dc10b9a2f2965fa2687c49d21af"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "corvid-1.0.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "2e7f8722779bedc8f6e380c974c5f8fe", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.5, <4", "size": 9874, "upload_time": "2020-01-12T23:44:22", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-01-12T23:44:22.767416Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/34/25/254ccdb5e7653eb